---

## ğŸ”„ Security Updates

### How We Handle Security Patches:

**Critical Vulnerabilities**:
- Immediate patch development
- Emergency release within 48-72 hours
- Clear upgrade instructions
- Post-mortem published after resolution

**High/Medium Vulnerabilities**:
- Patch included in next scheduled release
- Security advisory published with timeline
- Workarounds provided if available

**Low Vulnerabilities**:
- Fixed in normal development cycle
- Documented in changelog
- No special advisory needed

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Security Tools & Resources

### Recommended Tools:

**For Developers**:
- `npm audit` - Check for vulnerable dependencies
- `snyk` - Continuous security monitoring
- `OWASP ZAP` - Web application security testing
- `SonarQube` - Static code analysis

**For Deployers**:
- `fail2ban` - Intrusion prevention
- `ClamAV` - Antivirus scanning
- `Tripwire` - File integrity monitoring
- `OpenVAS` - Vulnerability scanning

### Learning Resources:
- [OWASP Top 10](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)
- [CWE/SANS Top 25](https://cwe.mitre.org/top25/)
- [NIST Cybersecurity Framework](https://www.nist.gov/cyberframework)
- [Post-Quantum Cryptography](https://csrc.nist.gov/projects/post-quantum-cryptography)

